I
\Bbb R
f:I\to \Bbb R
sup_{x\in I}|f'(x)|<\infty
f
c>0
|f(x)-f(y)|\le c|x-y|
\forall \;x,y\in I
|f'(t)|\le k
k\in \Bbb R^+
f(a)-f(b)=\int _a^b f'(t)dt
f(a)-f(b)=\int _a^b f'(t)dt
\Rightarrow |f(a)-f(b)|=|\int _a^b f'(t)dt|\le |\int _a^b |f'(t)|\;dt| \le |\int _a^b k\;dt|=|k(b-a)|
\Rightarrow |f(a)-f(b)| \le k\;|b-a|
